obo:ECO_0007719  a  owl:Class .

<http://identifiers.org/rgd/621008>
        a       owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_770  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Authors study the localization of Abi-1 in rat hippocampal cultures and rat brain using a monoclonal antibody against Abi-1. Immunoelectron microscopy revealed Abi-1 at postsynaptic densities. In line with this, immunostaining of Abi-1 showed colocalization of the protein with Shank3, a postsynaptic excitatory marker, while coimmunostaining with the presynaptic marker bassoon revealed a juxtaposed pattern, in agreement with the postsynaptic localization of Abi-1. Subcellular fractionation revealed enrichment of Abi-1 in PSD fractions.\n\n14/3/2017 Pim\n- Abi1 shown to interact directly with Shank3 but not with Shank1 (Fig.1). Shank3 is a typical PSD protein.. Experimental description: From M&M:\n- Cell culture experiments of rat hippocampal primary neurons (embryonic day-18-21; E18-21).\n- For isolation of subcellular protein factions and Western Blot analysis tissue from adult rats was homogenized." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0575-6950" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1585-539X" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_770" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

